]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"roleHeading":"API Collection","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular"},"abstract":[{"text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GUI app or the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI — both backed by the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a future release."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important"},{"text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Click the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cmd+N"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"into a new VM bundle."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Managing VMs","anchor":"Managing-VMs","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"type":"codeListing"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CapacityCheck","type":"reference"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":3,"text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"syntax":"bash","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"ssh","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"progress. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode"},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"text":" for detailed guidance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"EC2 Mac Setup","anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","type":"reference"},{"text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"releas